  based giving norms oriented to near-term impact might be more tractable than
  asset-based strategies requiring complex long-term optimization. However, the
  critique of using borrowing rates also applies to individual donors'
  decisions about consumption versus giving.

  POSITION: Methodological analysis of discount rate selection; identifies
  limits of financial economics for long-term social decisions.
  },
  keywords = {discount-rate, financial-economics, methodology, Low}
}

